ared heights of 1.83 and 1.88 meters on her first attempt, and 1,92 and 1,95 meters on her second attempt.\", \"from\": 328, \"to\": 455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 328, \"end\": 340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\", \"score\": 0.9999999363012668, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gerashchenko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Volodymyr_Herashchenko\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the second-best result in Group B, she advanced to the finals.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 487, \"end\": 494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_B\", \"score\": 0.9998663046653333, \"rank\": 0.00013180904641420222, \"text\": \"Group B\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_B\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_B\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was her best result of the season.\", \"from\": 524, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yuliia Levchenko did not manage to clear 1.83 meters in three attempts, therefore dropping out of the competition.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the start of the 2024 Olympic Games, Mahuchikh broke the 37-year-old world record previously held by Bulgaria's Stefka Kostadinova.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 789, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"score\": 0.9999994538817772, \"rank\": 5.383195465714358e-07, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefka_Kostadinova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefka Kostadinova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.or